Norm: matrices normalized prior complete analysis . “median”, matrices divided median; “mean”, divided mean; “none”, normalization performed. Normalizing ensures fast-evolving (slow-evolving) genes treated outliers. Normalization median better choice less sensitive outlier values. Default 1e-5. InitialOnly: Logical. TRUE, Initial state data computed. normalizeby: gene x species matrix normalized prior outlier detection, . parallel: Logical. computations parallelized possible? code: if (!requireNamespace("ape", quietly = TRUE))    install.packages("ape") trees <- ape::read.tree("treefile.tre") results <- phylter(trees, gene.names = names) phylter(X, bvalue = 0, distance = "patristic", k = 3, k2 = k, Norm = "median",   Norm.cutoff = 0.001, gene.names = NULL, test.island = TRUE,   verbose = TRUE, stop.criteria = 1e-5, InitialOnly = FALSE, normalizeby = "row",   parallel = TRUE) results$Final$Outliers # Get a summary: nb of outliers, gain in concordance, etc. summary(results)  # Show the number of species in each gene, and how many per gene are outliers plot(results, "genes")   # Show the number of genes where each species is found, and how many are outliers plot(results, "species")   # Compare before and after genes x species matrices, highlighting missing data and outliers  # identified (not efficient for large datasets) plot2WR(results)   # Plot the dispersion of data before and after outlier removal. One dot represents one  # gene x species association plotDispersion(results)   # Plot the genes x genes matrix showing pairwise correlation between genes plotRV(results)   # Plot optimization scores during optimization plotopti(results) write.phylter(results, file = "phylter.out")
